tensive powers to promote and protect the people’s welfare. By examining the Declaration in the context of British imperial debates, Pincus offers a nuanced portrait of the Founders’ intentions with profound political implications for today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / National.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030021618940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022444340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300224443/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY